Class PopularFeed

java.lang.Object
  com.payvment.continuuity.data.PopularFeed

public class PopularFeed
extends Object

A Payvment/Lish Popular Product Feed.

A popular feed is a descending score-ordered list of products.

This class is used to build and store a popular feed. It is feed a stream of scored products and performs any necessary sorting and aggregations.

JSON Format 

    {"popular" : [ { "product_id" : # , "score" : # }, ... ]}

addEntry

public void addEntry(Long product_id,
                     Long score)
Adds or updates the score of the specified product to this popular feed.

If entry for product exists, adds specified score to existing score, otherwise, initializes score to the specified score.

Parameters:
product_id - id of product
score - score of product

getFeed

public List<PopularFeed.PopularFeedEntry> getFeed(int limit)
Processes and returns the most popular feed entries in this feed in score descending order, up to the specified limit.

This is an expensive operation that performs sorting of all processed entries.

Parameters:
limit - maximum product entries
Returns:
list of product entries in descending score order
